<br>
The situation:<br>
    Corporate america has taken a major beating over the last few quarters.   9-11 has effected corporations in MANY ways, but then along comes the sudden realization that big business is not on the straight and narrow.  Yes so far only a handful have been questioned (Worldcomm, Enron, Arthur Anderson, Merck, etc etc..  yes Merck was absolved but they were added for a day or two.).  These companies are tanking, investors are gettign MAJORLY screwed.  Investor confidence is shakey.<br>
<br>
