That is what I suggest to all americans do before they vote.  Do the research.  Put forth the effort.  Don't take anything at face value. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucaelie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caelie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/17/02 1:06:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3470.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fair enough</span><hr size=1> Malevant, that could go on forever. Bottom line is what a person is looking for from their government or how they interpret the Constitution.<br>
<br>
Just because I'm a right winger doesn't mean I'm against racial equality. Difference is, I don't think its the Governments place to step in and tell employers who they have to hire.<br>
<br>
 Its not the governments place to support people forever with Welfare. Do I feel pity for the less fortunate? Of course I do, but thats where friends and family should come in and help care for them. Most Republicans feel that as long as the Government is taking care of people, why would the have any incentive to do better? When do people stand up and try to do better? I know if I was cold and hungry and not getting help from the government, I would definately try to better myself. I don't think anybody is saying that Democrats or Republicans are any better or any worse than the other. The whole argument is about each individuals opinion on how things should be run.<br>
<br>
Real Life government should be like the game EQ. What does the government do in EQ? Provides a military. Did EQ just give us stuff or did we have to earn it? Do they force the good and the evil characters or the black and white characters to play together. No, we do that on our own. <br>
90% of the players out there are genuinally good people and I'm sure we're not all of the same party. Yeah, EQ has its share of terriorists (KS'rs; Intentional Trainers; but they're delt with in time. I buff newbies in Misty Thicket, but not because the EQ government tells me I have to. I do it because I want to.<br>
<br>
I'm not a Right winger thats way out there. I even support seat belt laws, helmet laws, car seat laws etc. but I don't believe in hand-outs and thats what seperates me from the Left wingers that are way out there.<br>
<br>
My whole point is that this guy can't go pointing fingers at Bush no more than we can go pointing fingers at the Clinton administration just because they're not the party of his choice. As one guy posted, several factors have caused the decline in the economy. As far as Democraps, I was refering to Clinton specifically and those that condone his behavior. Theres a democrat in Georgia that I would vote for in a heartbeat if he was to run for President and thats Zell Miller. <p>Caelie<BR>
